               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18311201-225-person1753">
                  JAMES 
                  CHAMBERS
               <interp inst="t18311201-225-person1753" type="surname" value="CHAMBERS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18311201-225-person1753" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18311201-225-person1753" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a Policeman. On the evening of the 8th of November I was in the City-road, and saw the prisoner with something in a bag; I asked him what it was - he said a copper, which he had bought of a broker in Old-street-road; I took him to Mr. Dawson's shop, and while I went in to ask if he bought it there, he sat it down, and ran away - I followed, and took him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18311201-225-person1754">
                  JOHN 
                  DAWSON
               <interp inst="t18311201-225-person1754" type="surname" value="DAWSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18311201-225-person1754" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18311201-225-person1754" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live in Old-street-road, and am a <rs id="t18311201-225-viclabel1209" type="occupation">broker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18311201-225-victim1752 t18311201-225-viclabel1209"></join>. This copper was taken from outside my door.</p>
               <p>The prisoner put in a written Defence, stating that a man had taken him to the shop, and employed him to carry the copper, representing that he had purchased it.</p>
               <p>
